 in her rocking chair. She missed Raven and Lynn. Maybe some of that was worry too. <p>-:¦:- Yakut -:¦:-<BR>~Northern Amazon Shamaness~<BR>"An Eye for an Eye only makes the whole world blind."</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uchristannagoddessofpeace.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Christanna Goddess of Peace</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 46<br> <font color=#993300>(4/12/02 12:18:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=228.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://hometown.aol.com/cristalc15/images/tanna3.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Her New Life. Her New Home.</span><hr size=1> Tanna was rolling on the ground, being attacked by both Glory and Ariel. They were tickling her! &quot;No stop no no no!&quot; she whined playfully, trying to dodge their little fingers. Glory was especially good at this, she knew all the right places to attack. &quot;Yakut! Help! I'm being attacked!&quot; she called, and smiled when her comment made Glory laugh. <p><html> <center> <font face="vivaldi" size="+1" color="#ffc0cb"> ~ Christanna : Amazon Goddess of Shamanism ~ <br> Proud wife to Yakut  and mother to Yakut's children</font> </center> </html></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/ualysiaofscynthia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Alysia of Scynthia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 342<br> <font color=#993300>(4/12/02 1:47:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=228.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Checking up</span><hr size=1> Alysia came and knocked on the hut. Two gaurds stood behind the Queen. Nicala and Sariah naturally. Alysia-Samsara smiled to them both and then spoke.<br><br>&quot;We are all going out tonight for a hunt and were wondering if either of you would like to join us.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uyakutofthenorth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Yakut of the North</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 22<br> <font color=#993300>(4/12/02 5:59:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=228.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://hometown.aol.com/cristalc15/images/yakut.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Playing and Hunting...</span><hr size=1> Yakut stood and made her way over to Tanna and the kids. She laughed as she pinned Glory down and began tickling her.<br><br>Then a knock at the door. Yakut walked over to the door adjusting her shaman robes. As Tanna stood beside her Yakut opened the door smiling.<br><br>&quot;Yasoo, Vasilissa.&quot;<br><br>Yakut nodded to Nicala and Sariah.<br><br>&quot;Yasoo Athelfi.&quot;<br><br>Yakut turned her eyes to Tanna and her daughters. She returned her attention to Alysia.<br><br>&quot;I'm sorry to seem impolite my Queen but There are still some things I need to take care of.&quot;<br><br>It was odd now saying my Queen. Yakut normally used it but Now, she wasn't a Queen herself.<br><br>&quot;Though I would love to join you, I'm afraid I have things to tend to.&quot;<br><br>Yakut did indeed have things to take care of. Shyriana was supposed to visit and ask to become a Scynthian Athelfi. There was more than that of course.<br><br>&quot;Maybe later, I could introduce you to someone. She wishes to be apart of your tribe.&quot;<br><br>Yakut and Shyriana had recently been re-uinted and since have been inseperable. <p>-:¦:- Yakut -:¦:-<BR>~Northern Amazon Shamaness~<BR>"An Eye for an Eye only makes the whole world blind."</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/ualysiaofscynthia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Alysia of Scynthia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 343<br> <font color=#993300>(4/13/02 1:17:23 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=228.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> New Athelfi</span><hr size=1> Alysia gave a nod to Yakut.<br><br>&quot;Verywell Yakut. . . I would like to meet this new athelfi. Any amazon is welcome in Scynthia.&quot; She smiled lightly.<br><br>Another young amazon looked to Nicala and handed her a small scroll. Nicala looked at the brand on the edge of it and handed it to Alysia. &quot;A Letter from Vasilissa Raven.&quot;<br><br>Alysia smiled and took it opening the scroll in front of Yakut reading aloud:<br><br>~Vasilissa Alysia,<br>I am grateful for your assistance in Tanias Valley these past few days, the athelfi you sent to help me in the ceremonial rituals have been great. I hope that my Mother and sisters got to Scynthia and are doing well. Please send them my love. I am also grateful to you for your offer of protection over my tribe, as I have chosen to keep my mother's peace here in the Valley. Though I myself am a warrior, I will not raise up an army in bloodshed. Thank you for offering yours just in case. We never know when an enemy approaches. I hope this letter finds you all well.<br>Sincerly,<br>Vasilissa Raven~<br><br>Alysia smiled and handed the scroll to Yakut.<br><br>&quot;You should have this.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uchristannagoddessofpeace.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Christanna Goddess of Peace</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 47<br> <font color=#993300>(4/13/02 9:58:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=228.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://hometown.aol.com/cristalc15/images/tanna3.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: New Athelfi</span><hr size=1> Tanna gave a respectful bow to Alysia. &quot;Yasoo, Vasilissa,&quot; she said politely, and then grew quiet to listen to her wife speak. When they reached a breaking point, she excused herself quietly to check on the children. It wasn't a good idea to leave Glory alone with Ariel, or Ariel might wind up dressed up in some awful costume, or face painted like a streetwalker. She shuddered and went to check on them. She sighed when she saw them. They were sitting on Glory's bed, and Glory had Ariel in her lap and was reading her a book... <p><html> <center> <font face="vivaldi" size="+1" color="#ffc0cb"> ~ Christanna : Amazon Goddess of Shamanism ~ <br> Proud wife to Yakut  and mother to Yakut's children</font> </center> </html></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uyakutofthenorth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Yakut of the North</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 23<br> <font color=#993300>(4/13/02 12:02:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=228.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://hometown.aol.com/cristalc15/images/yakut.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Raven.</span><hr size=1> Yakut listened to the words from the letter and her heart filled with pride. She smiled as she was offered the scroll.<br><br>&quot;Thank you.&quot;<br><br>She said as she took the scroll into her hands.<br><br>&quot;Thank you very much.&quot;<br><br>Yakut looked back over her shoulder taking in a glance of her hut, her eyes soon returned to the Vasilissa.<br><br>&quot;How is Prigkipissa Isabelle? I have not seen her in a long while.&quot; <p>-:¦:- Yakut -:¦:-<BR>~Northern Amazon Shamaness~<BR>"An Eye for an Eye only makes the whole world blind."</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/ushamanessshyriana.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shamaness Shyriana</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#993300>(4/14/02 10:46:00 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=228.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Her New Life. Her New Home.</span><hr size=1> ::Shyriana entered the hut while looking over her shoulder back at the village. After they had first arrived, Shy had run off like a child to explore these new lands that she had been introduced to. She was beaming as she turned her gaze upon her sister and Tanna, then blinked in surprise as she saw Alysia standing there as well::<br><br>::The resemblance between Shyriana and Yakut was remarkable. They looked like exact copies of the other, all except for the dark tattoo that stretched across Shy's forehead. Shy's smile widened and she closed the gap between herself and the others::<br><br>&quot;Yasoo Sister, Tanna. It's a glorious day!&quot; She grinned, then turned to face Alysia. &quot;And Yasoo to you. My name is Shyriana. I am Yakut's twin. It is a pleasure to meet you.&quot; Of course, at that time, Shy had no idea that she was speaking to the Queen, so she saluted and gave a little bow of respect after her introduction, waiting to see who this new person would turn out to be:: <p>~*Shyrianna*~ ~*Fear me, love me, do as I say, And I will be your slave...*~</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uyakutofthenorth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Yakut of the North</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 24<br> <font color=#993300>(4/14/02 7:15:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=228.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://hometown.aol.com/cristalc15/images/yakut.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Shy!</span><hr size=1> Yakut grinned at her sisters site.<br><br>&quot;Yasoo Sis, this is Vasilissa Alysia of Scynthia.&quot;<br><br>She pointed at Aly. <p>-:¦:- Yakut -:¦:-<BR>~Northern Amazon Shamaness~<BR>"An Eye for an Eye only makes the whole world blind."</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/ualysiaofscynthia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Alysia of Scynthia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 344<br> <font color=#993300>(4/14/02 11:58:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=228.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>  . .. </span><hr size=1> She smiled lightly speaking of Belle.<br><br>&quot;She's spoke of comming home sometime soon.&quot;<br><br>Then the woman came in. Alysia was in shock of the resemblance, but then shrugged it off remember that she too had a twin sister. Gabrielle.<br><br>She nodded to the woman and smiled.<br><br>&quot;A pleasure to meet you. I am Alysia-Samsara. Queen of Scynthia.&quot;<br> <